The paper deals with the problem of identifying violent gang members using social network analysis and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of arrest metadata and classification algorithms, which are relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The study of gang violence and criminal behavior falls under the scope of cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Finally, the paper discusses operational issues related to law enforcement, which could be relevant to cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
